{"title_page": "2018 Garden Grove, California mayoral election", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox election\n| election_name      = Garden Grove, California mayoral election, 2018\n| flag_image         = Flag of Garden Grove, California.png\n| type               = Presidential\n| ongoing            = no\n| previous_election  = 2016 Garden Grove, California mayoral election\n| previous_year      = 2016\n| next_election      = 2020 Garden Grove, California mayoral election\n| next_year          = 2020\n| election_date      = November 6, 2018\n| image1             = \n| candidate1         =  '''Steve Jones'''\n| party1             = nonpartisan\n| popular_vote1      = '''33,788'''\n| percentage1        = '''84.4%'''\n| image2             = \n| candidate2         = Donald Taylor\n| party2             = Nonpartisan\n| popular_vote2      = 6,227\n| percentage2        = 15.6%\n| map_image          = 2018GGCAmayor.svg\n| map_size           = 325px\n| map_caption        = City council district results<br />\n'''Jones:''' {{legend0|#782121|80\u201390%}}\n| title              = Mayor\n| before_election    = Steve Jones\n| before_party       = Republican Party (United States)\n| after_election     = Steve Jones\n| after_party        = Republican Party (United States)\n}}\n{{ElectionsCA}}\n\nThe '''2018 Garden Grove, California mayoral election''' was held on November 6, 2018 to elect the mayor of [[Garden Grove, California]]. It saw the reelection of Steve Jones, a Republican.\n\nMunicipal elections in California are officially nonpartisan. In Garden Grove, the mayor serves a two-year term.\n\n==Candidates==\n===Declared===\n* Steve Jones, incumbent mayor of Garden Grove<ref name=\"results\"/>\n* Donald Taylor<ref name=\"results\"/>\n\n==Results==\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = 2018 Garden Grove, California mayoral election<ref name=\"results\">[https://www.ocvote.com/fileadmin/live/gen2018/results.htm]</ref>\n}} \n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n| party      = Nonpartisan\n| candidate  = Steve Jones (incumbent)\n| votes      = 33,788\n| percentage = 84.4%\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| party      = Nonpartisan\n| candidate  = Donald Taylor\n| votes      = 6,227\n| percentage = 15.6%\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = 40,015\n| percentage = 100.0%\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Results by city council district===\nJones won all 6 districts. <span style=background:#ffb6b5>Red</span> represents districts won by Jones.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! colspan=6| Results by district<ref name=\"results\"/>\n|-\n! rowspan=2| District\n! colspan=2| Jones\n! colspan=2| Taylor\n! Total\n|-\n! Votes !! % !! Votes !! % !! data-sort-type=number|Votes\n|- {{party shading/Republican}}\n| 1 || '''''7,682''''' || '''83.5%''' || ''1,522'' || 16.5% || ''9,204''\n|- {{party shading/Republican}}\n| 2 || '''''6,096''''' || '''83.7%''' || ''1,184'' || 16.3% || ''7,280''\n|- {{party shading/Republican}}\n| 3 || '''''5,197''''' || '''84.6%''' || ''948'' || 15.4% || ''6,145''\n|- {{party shading/Republican}}\n| 4 || '''''5,594''''' || '''85.9%''' || ''917'' || 14.1% || ''6,511''\n|- {{party shading/Republican}}\n| 5 || '''''5,453''''' || '''84.5%''' || ''1,001'' || 15.5% || ''6,454''\n|- {{party shading/Republican}}\n| 6 || '''''3,766''''' || '''85.2%''' || ''655'' || 14.8% || ''4,421''\n|-\n! Totals !! 33,788 !! 84.4% !! 6,227 !! 15.6% !! 40,015\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{United States elections, 2018}}\n\n[[Category:2018 California elections|Garden Grove]]\n[[Category:Local elections in California]]\n[[Category:2018 United States mayoral elections|Garden Grove]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox Election\n| election_name      = Garden Grove, California mayoral election, 2018\n| flag_image         = Flag of Garden Grove, California.png\n| type               = Presidential\n| ongoing    