adcasting Corporation|accessdate=3 July 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Amazon Adventure'' || Series 2, episodes:\n* ''Amazon Adventure'' (special)\n* ''Bowhead Whales''\n* ''Damselfish''\n* ''Jawfish''\n* ''Fiddler Crabs''\n* ''Manta Rays''\n| 2 January 2014<ref>{{cite web|title=Octonauts - Amazon Adventure {{!}} DVD|url=https://shop.abc.net.au/products/octonauts-dvd-amazon-adventure|website=ABC Shop|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation|accessdate=3 July 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Calling all GUPs!'' || Series 2, episodes:\n* ''Porcupine Puffer''\n* ''Scared Sperm Whale''\n* ''Long Arm Squid''\n* ''Swashbuckling Swordfish''\n* ''Manatees''\n* ''Saltwater Crocodile''\n* ''Humphead Parrotfish''\n| 11 June 2014<ref>{{cite web|title=Octonauts - Calling all GUPs {{!}} DVD|url=https://shop.abc.net.au/products/octonauts-calling-all-gups-dvd|website=ABC Shop|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation|accessdate=3 July 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Deep Sea Adventure!'' || Series 2 and 3, episodes:\n* ''Mariana Trench Adventure'' (special)\n* ''Scared Sperm Whale''\n* ''Long-Arm Squid''\n* ''Gulper Eels''\n* ''Sea Pigs''\n* ''Yeti Crab''\n| 3 September 2014<ref>{{cite web|title=Octonauts - Deep Sea Adventure! {{!}} DVD|url=https://shop.abc.net.au/products/octonauts-deep-sea-adventure-dvd|website=ABC Shop|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation|accessdate=3 July 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Flappity Flippers!'' || Series 2 and 3, episodes:\n* ''Cone Snails''\n* ''Harbour Seal''\n* ''Lionfish''\n* ''Mimic Octopus''\n* ''Mudskippers''\n* ''Lion's Mane Jellyfish''\n* ''Leafy Sea Dragons''\n| 7 January 2015<ref>{{cite web|title=Octonauts - Flappity Flippers {{!}} DVD|url=https://shop.abc.net.au/products/octonauts-flappity-flippers-dvd|website=ABC Shop|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation|accessdate=3 July 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Great Arctic Adventure'' || Series 2 and 3, episodes:\n* ''Great Arctic Adventure'' (special)\n* ''Triggerfish''\n* ''Humpback Whales''\n* ''Barracudas''\n* ''Urchin Invasion''\n* ''Siphonophore\n| 3 June 2015<ref>{{cite web|title=Octonauts - Great Arctic Adventure {{!}} DVD|url=https://shop.abc.net.au/products/octonauts-dvd-great-arctic|website=ABC Shop|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation|accessdate=3 July 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Here Come the Vegimals'' || Series 3, episodes:\n* ''Very Vegimals Christmas'' (special)\n* ''Water Bears''\n* ''Pelicans''\n* ''Red Rock Crabs''\n* ''Sea Sponge''\n* ''Immortal Jellyfish''\n| 4 November 2015<ref>{{cite web|title=Octonauts - Here Come The Vegimals {{!}} DVD|url=https://shop.abc.net.au/products/octonauts-here-come-the-vegimals-dvd|website=ABC Shop|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation|accessdate=3 July 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Over Under Adventure'' || Series 3, episodes:\n* ''Over Under Adventure'' (special)\n* ''Walrus Pups''\n* ''Hidden Lake''\n* ''Tree Lobsters''\n* ''Mantis Shrimp''\n* ''Convict Fish''\n| 2 March 2016<ref>{{cite web|title=Octonauts - Over Under Adventure {{!}} DVD|url=https://shop.abc.net.au/products/octonauts-over-under-adventure-dvd|website=ABC Shop|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation|accessdate=3 July 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''The Great Swamp Search'' || TBC || 6 July 2016<ref>{{cite web|title=Octonauts - The Great Swamp Search {{!}} DVD|url=https://shop.abc.net.au/products/octonauts-the-great-swamp-search-dvd|website=ABC Shop|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation|accessdate=3 July 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\nThe first four DVDs have sold together as the ''Octonauts Starter Pack'' since 2016.\n\n==Spin-offs==\n\nThe Octonauts brand has been licensed by the production company for numerous spin-off activities. These include [[Octonauts Rollercoaster Adventure]], a themed rollercoaster within the [[CBeebies#CBeebies Land|CBeebies Land]] of [[Alton Towers]] theme park and themed bedrooms with the CBeebies Land Hotel. There is also a travelling live show called ''Octonauts Live'', which has toured in the U.S.<ref>{{cite |url=https://www.octonautsliveus.com |title= Octonauts Live!}}</ref> and other countries.\n\nAn ''Octonauts'' app was launched for iOS on 17 November 2016, produced in partnership with Night and Day Studios.<ref>{{cite press release |url=http://silvergatemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Silvergate-Media-Octonauts-app-launched-17-November-20161.pdf |title=Silvergate and Night & Day Studios launch first ever Octonauts app |location=New York and London |date=17 November 2016 |access-date=2017-03-06 |publisher=Silvergate Media |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170307123850/http://silvergatemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Silvergate-Media-Octonauts-app-launched-17-November-20161.pdf |archive-date=7 March 2017 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n* {{BBC programme}}\n\n===Channels===\n* [http://disney.go.com/disneyjunior/octonauts Octonauts on Disney Junior US]\n* [http://www.abc.net.au/abcforkids/shows/s3106715.htm Octonauts on ABC 4 Kids]\n* [http://www.tudiscoverykids.com/personajes/octonautas Octonauts on Discovery Kids]\n* [http://discoverykidsbrasil.uol.com.br/personagens/octonautas Octonauts on Discovery Kids Brazil]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20130406154810/http://videos.tf1.fr/octonauts/ Octonauts on TF1]\n* [http://www.tfou.fr/les-octonauts/videos Octonauts on TFOU]\n* [http://www.treehousetv.com/show/octonauts Octonauts on Treehouse]\n\n===Other links===\n* {{Official website|http://www.octonauts.com}} (by the book's authors: [[Meomi Design]])\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20111018101504/http://www.heroesforkids.co.uk/octonauts.html Official Octonauts store UK ]\n* [http://www.theoctonauts.com/ Chorion's Octonauts TV site]\n* [http://disneyjunior.com/the-octonauts Octonauts on Disney Junior]\n\n{{Disney Junior}}\n{{Annie Award for Best Animated Television Production}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Octonauts}}\n[[Category:2010s British animated television series]]\n[[Category:2010s British children's televisi